The paper describes a deep learning approach for automated brain hemorrhage detection from CT scans, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of attention and recurrent neural network layers also suggests relevance to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analysis of medical images, which could potentially fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
